eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 10 Years
Maximum age: 99 Years
Current immunosuppression (cancer, autoimmune disease) or taking immunosuppressive drugs

Women of childbearing potential, unless using effective contraception while on study
             drug.

Uncontrolled intercurrent illness including, but not limited to, any of the following: 
* Ongoing or active infection 
* Symptomatic congestive heart failure
* Unstable angina pectoris
* Cardiac arrhythmia including QTc > 450 msec
* Psychiatric illness/social situations that would limit compliance with study requirements

Related organ or tissue impairment (CRAB symptoms: anemia, hypercalcemia, lytic bone
             lesions, renal insufficiency, hyperviscosity, amyloidosis or recurrent infections)
Magnesium < 0.9 mg/dl (< 0.4 mmol/L) or > 3 mg/dl (> 1.23 mmol/L) despite intervention to normalize levels

groups.description: Patients receive pembrolizumab IV over 30 minutes on day 1. Patients also receive anti-FGFR3 monoclonal antibody B-701 IV over 30-90 minutes on days 1 and 8 of course 1, and day 1 of all subsequent courses. Courses repeat every 21 days in the absence of disease progression or unacceptable toxicity.

outcome_measures.measure: Dose of melphalan required for the establishment of peripheral T cell tolerance with concomitant immune reconstitution and acceptable regimen related toxicity (Phase I)

outcome_measures.analysis_method: TTF will be examined using Kaplan-Meier methods.
outcome_measures.measure: Time to treatment failure (TTF) (Expansion cohort only)

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Will be estimated using Kaplan-Meier method.
outcome_measures.measure: Time to total-ALP progression defined as decline from baseline as >= 25% increase from the nadir value
